http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Stray-dog-carrying-severed-head-creates-flutter/article13978636.ece

Fear gripped the residents of Seetharamaraju Colony near the Elamanchali Railway Station in the district on Saturday when a dog was seen carrying the head of a man in its mouth.On getting information from the local people, the police rushed to the spot and recovered the head of the man, which was severed from his body. The police initially suspected that the victim was beheaded by someone.Investigation revealed that the man, aged around 40 years, had committed suicide by falling under a train. Stray dogs took away the head soon after the incident.Elamanchili Inspector K Venkata Rao is investigating the case.